<h1 class="docs-header">Typography</h1>
<p>This is where BaseWeb defines our most basic typographic elements. This includes things like base font styles, headings, links and emphasis elements.</p>

<h2 class="docs-header">Headings</h2>
<p>Heading elements are used to describe the topic of the section it introduces. BaseWeb defines styles for headings <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code>.</p>

<pre class="language-markup"><code>&lt;h1&gt;h1. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;h2. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;h3. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;h4. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;h5. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h6&gt;h6. BaseWeb Heading&lt;/h6&gt;</code></pre>

